Additionally, the paper proposes an automated tool for generating both FPGA- and ASIC-based DNN chip implementations, which is a topic that falls under the hardware architecture sub-field. 

The paper also relates to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it deals with DNNs, which are a type of AI model. The paper proposes a tool that can automatically generate DNN chips, which can be used to accelerate the execution of DNNs, a topic that is relevant to the AI sub-field. 

The sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant because the paper proposes a tool that can optimize the design of DNN chips based on the target design metrics. This involves balancing the resources of the chip and selecting the appropriate IP blocks, which is a topic that falls under the systems and control sub-field. 

The sub-category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is relevant because the paper proposes a tool that can generate both FPGA- and ASIC-based DNN chip implementations.
